		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical History</head>
			
		<p>Abel E. Powers was a tinsmith in the post-township of Eaton in Madison County, New York.   His customers included residents of Eaton, Morrisville, and Peterborough.</p></bioghist>
		
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>The <emph render="bold">Abel E. Powers Ledger</emph> consists of 75+ pages recording the tinsmith's transactions from 1845 to 1850.   Each page is headed with the name of an individual or business followed by a dated and itemized list of transactions and the price paid.</p>
		</scopecontent>
		
